result.execSummary:
The defendant Ashley Marie Salaj was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Felony, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).
  • Retail Theft - Intentionally Take (<=$500), a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.50(1m)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes:
Court orders bond amount posted shall be applied and balance owed shall be paid from bond posted in 22CF276 per stipulation.

lf extended supervision is revoked and the defendant will have a mandatory release from prison, a civil judgment shall be entered for the balance due. 

Defendant shall provide a biological specimen for DNA analysis.  Defendant has the right to request expungement of DNA analysis in writing through the Department of Justice.
Bond amount posted shall be applied.  Defendant stipulates to the restitution amounts in 22CF232 restitution is $6.48 plus surcharge and 22CF276 restitution is $5.00 plus surcharge.
Defendant shall undergo an AODA assessment and comply with recommendations.
Defendant shall have no contact with Walmart Stores in Wisconsin.
Defendant shall participate in all counseling, assessments, and/or treatment programs directed by the probation agent and comply with treatment recommendations.

supervisions.notes:
With Huber privileges consistent with the rules of the jail while the inmate maintains a minimum security status. The defendant, at the discretion of the Sheriff, may perform community service work as an inmate worker in the county jail and shall earn statutory good time for same.
Concurrent with: Count 1

miscConds.notes: All conditions of probation as contained in Count 1 are inclusive of Count 5.
